Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 1cm pieces. Pop the aubergine on a #baking tray{} in one layer, drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @chermoula spice mix{1} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until crisp and golden, ~{20-22%minutes}, turning halfway.

Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks) and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1/2%can} in a #sieve{}. Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the flesh onto a #board{}. Chop into 1cm cubes.

Heat a #medium frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil!) Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{15%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}. TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily. Once toasted transfer to a #bowl{} for later and set aside.

Pop your #frying pan{} back on medium high heat and add a drizzle of @oil{}. Add the garlic and fry for until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add the chickpeas and @smoked paprika{1} and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes{1} and season with salt, pepper and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}. Bring to the boil, and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, fill and boil your #kettle{}. Put the @Moroccan Medley Couscous{100%g} in a bowl. Pour the boiling @water{} for the couscous (see ingredients for amount) into the bowl, cover tightly with #cling film{}. Leave to the side for ~{5%minutes} or until ready to serve. Pop the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} in a bowl and stir in half the mint, season with salt and pepper.

Once everything is cooked, taste the tomatoey chickpeas and add salt and pepper if you feel they need it. Drizzle the @honey{15%ml} on the roasted aubergine and toss to coat. Fluff up the couscous and divide between your bowls. Cover one third with the roasted aubergine, one third with the tomatoey chickpeas and one third with the chopped avocado. Drizzle it all with the minty yogurt and sprinkle on the toasted almonds and remaining mint. Enjoy!